you'd give him away too.

138
00:15:52,145 --> 00:15:53,695
Does he even love me?

139
00:15:56,545 --> 00:15:58,195
Why would you say that?

140
00:15:58,735 --> 00:16:00,285
I didn't love my dad.

141
00:16:01,464 --> 00:16:03,126
Not even when you were Oliver's age?

142
00:16:05,195 --> 00:16:06,195
Sure.

143
00:16:07,285 --> 00:16:10,300
I did love him back then,
but it was unrequited love.

144
00:16:10,775 --> 00:16:12,927
You'll have to explain that
to me, Luke.

145
00:16:13,755 --> 00:16:17,307
My father was the dean of students and
basketball coach at my middle school.

146
00:16:18,015 --> 00:16:21,019
He was in charge of every breath
my brother and I took.

147
00:16:21,215 --> 00:16:22,565
When we did well,

148
00:16:23,725 --> 00:16:25,975
that's just what he expected of us.

149
00:16:26,975 --> 00:16:28,625
And when we screwed up,

150
00:16:30,675 --> 00:16:33,531
well, let's just say
