161
00:17:08,065 --> 00:17:11,265
Then my dad came out of her bathroom
and started screaming at us.

162
00:17:12,265 --> 00:17:13,810
What did you guys do?

163
00:17:13,935 --> 00:17:17,235
What could we do?
We got on our bikes and we rode home.

164
00:17:18,165 --> 00:17:21,115
And then I was lying awake
that night in the bed

165
00:17:22,825 --> 00:17:25,111
and I realized my father's
secretary's living room

166
00:17:25,236 --> 00:17:27,136
looked exactly like our living room.

167
00:17:30,095 --> 00:17:33,345
Every piece of furniture
was exactly the same as ours.

168
00:17:35,455 --> 00:17:37,605
He must've bought it all for her.

169
00:17:39,925 --> 00:17:42,725
My brother told my mother
and shit hit the fan.

170
00:17:44,605 --> 00:17:46,805
She packed us up and we left town.

171
00:17:47,555 --> 00:17:50,855
We only ever heard from him
when he sent his check every month.

172
00:17:51,665 --> 00:17:54,165
He was good about the money,
I'll give him that.

173
00:17:56,745 --> 00:17:58,645
But we didn't wanna see him.

174
00:18:00,865 --> 00:18:03,079
I mean, he sure didn't wanna see us.

175
00:18:05,295 --> 00:18:07,195
He never met Bess or Oliver.

176
00:18:10,045 --> 00:18:12,088
And when he died,
it was like a formality.

177
00:18:14,275 --> 00:18:15,425
But lately...

178
00:18:21,025 --> 00:18:23,025
It's like he's laughing at me.

179
00:18:25,885 --> 00:18:27,535
I did everything right.

180
00:18:28,494 --> 00:18:30,414
I proposed to Bess
when I got her pregnant.

181
00:18:30,539 --> 00:18:33,089
I worked like a dog
to make a good home.

182
00:18:33,715 --> 00:18:35,815
I never raised a hand to Oliver.

183
00:18:39,025 --> 00:18:41,575
And now I feel like I'm standing
right where my father stood.

184
00:18:44,825 --> 00:18:47,770
You know, just because you're getting
a divorce, that doesn't...

185
00:18:47,895 --> 00:18:50,251
that doesn't mean
you're turning into your father.

186
00:18:51,075 --> 00:18:53,825
And it doesn't mean that
you're gonna lose your son.

187
00:18:59,415 --> 00:19:02,365
But that's exactly
what it feels like I'm doing.

188
00:19:02,931 --> 00:19:06,225
It's inevitable that sometimes
you'll remind yourself of your father.

189
00:19:07,785 --> 00:19:10,585
You see how you wound
your own children so...

190
00:19:11,305 --> 00:19:13,255
so badly without even trying.

191
00:19:14,705 --> 00:19:17,305
Suddenly, you almost
understand how he...

192
00:19:18,955 --> 00:19:21,105
he could hurt you the way he did.

193
00:19:23,485 --> 00:19:26,266
But you don't have
to become like him.

194
00:19:26,391 --> 00:19:28,747
You're not doomed
to live your father's life.

195
00:19:28,945 --> 00:19:30,645
You have a choice.

196
00:19:46,095 --> 00:19:48,345
I think our session is almost over.

197
00:19:48,885 --> 00:19:51,668
Would you like to say anything
to Oliver before you go?

198
00:19:52,795 --> 00:19:54,695
Yeah, if we still have time.

199
00:20:01,785 --> 00:20:04,535
Oliver, do you want
to come in for a minute?

200
00:20:10,785 --> 00:20:12,835
I'm sorry you had
a bad day at school.

201
00:20:14,525 --> 00:20:15,525
It's okay.

202
00:20:17,085 --> 00:20:19,235
What do you say
